description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 0094 channel (as well as AIA 131) is designed to study solar flares. It
measures extremely hot temperatures around 6 million Kelvin (10.8 million F).
It can take images every 2 seconds (instead of 10) in a reduced field of view
in order to look at flares in more detail.

**Where:** Flaring regions of the corona

**Wavelength:** 94 angstroms (0.0000000094 m) = Extreme Ultraviolet/soft
X-rays

**Primary ions seen:** 17 times ionized iron (Fe XVIII)

**Characteristic temperature:** 6 million K (10.8 million F)

AIA 0094 channel (as well as AIA 131) is designed to study solar flares. It
measures extremely hot temperatures around 6 million Kelvin (10.8 million F).
It can take images every 2 seconds (instead of 10) in a reduced field of view
in order to look at flares in more detail.

**Where:** Flaring regions of the corona

**Wavelength:** 94 angstroms (0.0000000094 m) = Extreme Ultraviolet/soft
X-rays

**Primary ions seen:** 17 times ionized iron (Fe XVIII)

**Characteristic temperature:** 6 million K (10.8 million F)

file_name: File:Madrid y Chongquin rubrican su colaboración en un memorando 04.jpg
description: ['Spanish judge and politician, mayor of Madrid']
parsed caption:
La alcaldesa de Madrid Manuela Carmena, ha suscrito esta mañana un memorando
de colaboración (MOU) con el Ayuntamiento de Chongquin, ciudad china con cerca
de 19 millones de habitantes, cuyos representantes municipales se encuentran
en la capital interesados en la gestión de Madrid en temas relacionados, sobre
todo, con el desarrollo urbano, la movilidad, la cultura y el turismo. Este
acuerdo, que se suma a los suscritos la pasada semana con otras cuatro
ciudades, en ese caso de Iberoamérica, muestra el impulso dado por el Gobierno
municipal a la internacionalización de Madrid.

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 0171 channel is especially good at showing coronal loops - the arcs
extending off of the Sun where plasma moves along magnetic field lines. The
brightest spots seen here are locations where the magnetic field near the
surface is exceptionally strong.

**Where:** Quiet corona and upper transition region

**Wavelength:** 171 angstroms (0.0000000171 m) = Extreme Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** 8 times ionized iron (Fe IX)

**Characteristic temperature:** 1 million K (1.8 million F)

market, butchers stalls and a corn exchange" (
<http://www.bidefordtown.co.uk/Bideford%20Town%20Council%203.htm> ). The

central row of 24 shops along the contour. This is the southern side.

description: ['Canadian singer']
parsed caption:
Pour célébrer les 25 ans des FrancoFolies de Montréal, le président, Alain
Simard, a eu l'idée de réunir 25 artistes (ou groupes) qui chanteraient chacun
LA chanson de leur répertoire la plus connue du public. Le spectacle a eu lieu
lundi le 17 juin 2013 à partir de 21:00 à la place des Festivals. Dans
l'ordre, sont apparus : Karim Ouellet, Ariane Moffatt, Richard Séguin,
Corneille, Lisa LeBlanc, Daniel Lavoie, Mara Tremblay, Mes Aïeux, Luc De
Larochelière, Dumas, Isabelle Boulay, Yann Perreau, Laurence Jalbert, Stefie
Shock, Michel Rivard, Pierre Lapointe, Dan Bigras, Paul Piché, Vincent
Vallières, Les Respectables, Damien Robitaille, Loco Locass, Daniel Boucher,
Marjo et Éric Lapointe.

depicts: ['The Cross-border Parcel Delivery Services (Amendment) (No.2) (EU Exit) Regulations 2020']
description: ['UK Statutory Instrument 2020\xa0No. 1036']
parsed caption:
These Regulations are made in exercise of the powers conferred by section 8(1)
of the European Union (Withdrawal) Act 2018 (c. 16) (“the 2018 Act”) in order
to address failures of retained EU law to operate effectively and other
deficiencies (in particular under section 8(2)(a), (d) and (g)) arising from
the withdrawal of the United Kingdom from the European Union.

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 0304 channel is especially good at showing areas where cooler dense plumes
of plasma (filaments and prominences) are located above the visible surface of
the Sun. Many of these features either can't be seen or appear as dark lines
in the other channels. The bright areas show places where the plasma has a
high density.

**Where:** Upper chromosphere and lower transition region

**Wavelength:** 304 angstroms (0.0000000304 m) = Extreme Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** singly ionized helium (He II)

**Characteristic temperature:** 50,000 K (90,000 F)

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 0193 channel highlights the outer atmosphere of the Sun - called the
corona - as well as hot flare plasma. Hot active regions, solar flares, and
coronal mass ejections will appear bright here. The dark areas - called
coronal holes - are places where very little radiation is emitted, yet are the
main source of solar wind particles.

**Where:** Corona and hot flare plasma

**Wavelength:** 193 angstroms (0.0000000193 m) = Extreme Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** 11 times ionized iron (Fe XII)

**Characteristic temperature:** 1.25 million K (2.25 million F)

file_name: File:Weissenbach an der Triesting - Peilstein, Aussichtsturm.JPG
description: [None]
parsed caption:
Aussichtsturm auf dem Gipfel des 716 m hohen
[Peilsteins](https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peilstein_\(Wienerwald\)
"de:Peilstein \(Wienerwald\)").  
Der 12 m hohe Turm wurde 2013 direkt an der Ostseite des
[Peilsteinhauses](https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peilsteinhaus
"de:Peilsteinhaus") errichtet und dient gleichzeitig als
[Fluchttreppe](https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluchttreppe "de:Fluchttreppe")
für das Ober- und Dachgeschoss des Hauses. Zuvor gab es auf dem Peilstein auch
schon eine [Peilstein-Warte](https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peilstein-Warte
"de:Peilstein-Warte"), die jedoch im Zuge des Zweiten Weltkrieges stark
beschädigt wurde und daher 1947 vollständig abgetragen werden musste.

([Protocols](//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:CJK_stroke_order:Protocols

[link](https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Stroke_Order_Project/Graphics_guidelines/Bitmap_animations_using_GIMP)
are the official guidelines.

file_name: File:Ayuntamiento y sindicatos suscriben un acuerdo para homologar al personal laboral con el funcionario (02).jpg
description: ['Spanish judge and politician, mayor of Madrid']
parsed caption:
La alcaldesa de Madrid, Manuela Carmena, ha firmado con los sindicatos CC.OO,
UGT, CSIF y CSIT, un acuerdo que culmina el proceso de clasificación del
personal laboral municipal, pendiente desde el 2006. Gracias a este acuerdo,
que supone 9,5 millones de euros para las arcas municipales, se normaliza, a
partir del 1 de julio, la situación de los cerca de 4.200 trabajadores
laborales que tiene el Ayuntamiento, al equiparar su situación a la del
personal funcionario, abriéndoles además el camino de su promoción
profesional.

file_name: File:Memorandum of Understanding signing event celebrating America’s Longleaf Restoration Initiative (ALRI) on November 15, 2023, at the United States Department of Agriculture (USDA) in Washington, D.C. - 24.jpg
description: ['department of the US government']
parsed caption:
Jamelle Ellis, Longleaf for All answers panel questions during America’s
Longleaf Restoration Initiative Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) signing on
Wednesday, November 15, 2023, at the U.S. Department of Agriculture Jamie L.
Whitten Building Patio in Washington, D.C. The America's Longleaf Restoration
Initiative (ALRI) is a collaborative effort of multiple public and private
sector partners that actively supports range-wide efforts to restore and
conserve longleaf pine ecosystems. The vision of the partners involved in the
ALRI is to have functional, viable longleaf pine ecosystems with the full
spectrum of ecological, economic, and social values inspired through the
voluntary involvement of motivated organizations and individuals. (USDA photo
by Tom Witham)

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 0171 channel is especially good at showing coronal loops - the arcs
extending off of the Sun where plasma moves along magnetic field lines. The
brightest spots seen here are locations where the magnetic field near the
surface is exceptionally strong.

**Where:** Quiet corona and upper transition region

**Wavelength:** 171 angstroms (0.0000000171 m) = Extreme Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** 8 times ionized iron (Fe IX)

**Characteristic temperature:** 1 million K (1.8 million F)

parsed caption:
Die Tableaus mit Eisenbahnfahrkarten wurden von dem Sammler und Opernsänger
Fritz Hellmuth zwischen dem Ende des 19. Jahrhunderts bis ca. 1925 erstellt.
Hierfür sammelte er weltweit auf eigenen Reisen Fahrkarten oder ließ sich
diese von den Eisenbahngesellschaften zuschicken. Die Sammlung wurde 1926 vom
Berliner Verkehrs- und Baumuseum übernommen und ist heute im Historischen
Archiv der Stiftung Deutsches Technikmuseum Berlin zugänglich. Das vorliegende
Tableau zeigt 47 Fahrkarten.

[Malvaceae](https://www.flickr.com/search/?q=Malvaceae&w=91314344@N00&m=tags)
(mallow family) » _[Sida
acuta](https://www.flickr.com/search/?q=Sidaacuta&w=91314344@N00&m=tags)_

**SEE-duh** \-- in Greek, a type of water lily; although now a name for a type
of mallow **a-KEW-ta** \-- sharp angles; sharpened to a point

**commonly known as** : common fanpetals, ironweed, southern sida, teaweed,
wireweed • **Hindi** : महाबल mahabal • **Kannada** : ವಿಷಕಡ್ಡಿ vishakaddi •
**Malayalam** : മഞ്ഞക്കുറുന്തൊട്ടി maannakkurgunthotti • **Marathi** : बल
bala, चिकना chikna, जंगली मेथी jungali methi, पाटा pata • **Sanskrit** : बल
bala, पट्ट patta • **Tamil** : பொன்முசுட்டை ponmucuttai, வட்டத்திருப்பி
vattatirippi • **Telugu** : నేల బెండ nela benda, విషబొడ్డి visah-boddi

**Native** : pantropical

**References** : [Flowers of
India](http://www.flowersofindia.in/catalog/slides/Common%20Wireweed.html) •
[PIER species info](http://www.hear.org/pier/species/sida_acuta.htm) • [Forest
Flora of Andhra
Pradesh](http://forest.ap.nic.in/Forest%20Flora%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh/files/ff0181.htm)

file_name: File:152. Geburtstag der Hofer Wärschtlamänner HOF08373 RAW-Export.png
description: ['Anniversary event in the courtyard of the town hall in honor of the Hofer Wärschtlamänner (September 06, 2023)']
parsed caption:
View of the anniversary event in honor of the Hof Wärschtlamänner on the
evening of September 06, 2023. The citizens of Hof were invited to listen to
music and an address by Mayor Eva Döhla, who awarded the Golden Wärschtlamo
2023 in honor of decades of commitment to the culinary arts. People could take
a seat at the beer benches, and in the eastern part of the courtyard they
could pick up beer and Wärschtla with rolls and mustard. The Wärschtla were
handed out by Eva Döhla (mayor), Angela Bier (mayor) and Sebastian Auer
(mayor), among others. The event went from 5 to 8 pm. Here you can see a
damaged sign.

file_name: File:Henri Béchard - Thebes, The Colossi of Memnon - 2006.119 - Cleveland Museum of Art.tif
description: ['ancient Egyptian statues']
parsed caption:
As more photographers shot the same monuments,depictions became
formulaic.Numerous photographers produced almost identical images,as
demonstrated in these two views of the Colossi of Memnon. Shot from different
sides but about the same distance, both images employ an angled view and use
Egyptian servants and guides as local color and indexes of scale. Captions and
artists’ signatures were often written in reverse on the negatives so that
they would automatically become part of each print. Sometimes, as in the Beato
image, the artist or his assistant was care less.

industry as a fraction of total employed persons aged 15 and over, in

above and below the median value.

file_name: File:Royal visit to IMO's Maritime Safety Committee (32330374688).jpg
description: ['Secretary-General, International Maritime Organization (IMO), London']
parsed caption:
Her Royal Highness The Princess Royal visited IMO Headquarters in London. The
Princess Royal was received by IMO Secretary-General Kitack Lim and addressed
the 100th session of the Maritime Safety Committee (MSC) and took a keen
interest in the proceedings, as the Committee discussed measures to enhance
maritime security and piracy and armed robbery against ships.

VESSELS—THE PROW, POOP, RUDDER, OARS, MASTS,SAILS, CORDAGE, BULWARKS,
ANCHORS—BIREMES, TRIREMES, QUADRIREMES,QUINQUEREMES—THE GRAND GALLEY OF
PTOLEMY PHILOPATOR—ROMAN VES-SELS—THEIR NAVY—MIMIC SEA-FIGHTS—THE FIVE VOYAGES
OF ANTIQUITY. The prow or foredeck of Greek vessels was ornamented onboth
sides by figures in mosaic or painted. An eye on each sideof the cutwater, as
is represented above, was a very commonembellishment. A projection from the
head of the prow, pointedor covered with brass, and intended to damage an
enemy uponcollision, was often in the shape of a wild beast, or helmet, oreven
the neck of a swan. Below this was the rostrum or beak,which consisted of a
beam armed with sharp and solid irons.They were at first above the water; but

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 0211 channel (as well as AIA 335) highlights the active region of the
outer atmosphere of the Sun - the corona. Active regions, solar flares, and
coronal mass ejections will appear bright here. The dark areas - called
coronal holes - are places where very little radiation is emitted, yet are the
main source of solar wind particles.

**Where:** Active regions of the corona

**Wavelength:** 211 angstroms (0.0000000211 m) = Extreme Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** 13 times ionized iron (Fe XIV)

**Characteristic temperature:** 2 million K (3.6 million F)

description: ['form of long trunk hose (paned breeches) with very full, unpadded linings hanging loosely between the panes, worn in Northern Europe in the 16th century']
parsed caption:
Tröja med skört av brunviolett siden i tuskaft och fodrad med naturfärgat
linne och mörkt gulorange guldbrokad. Tröjan är dekorerad med guldbroderier
och gyllene paljetter. Längd mitt fram 450 mm, bredd mitt fram 365 mm.
Skörtlängd 100 mm. Rygglängd mitt bak 500 mm, därav liv 400 mm. Ryggbredd 460
mm. Axelsöm 150 mm. Ärmlängd 705 mm. Största ärmvidden 380 mm. Ärmvidd nedtill
250 mm. Kragens höjd mitt fram 30 mm och mitt bak 55 mm. Längs med vänster
framkant 29 st 20 mm långa knapphål kantade med gult silke. Framkanterna har
hårda inlägg, längd 410 mm och bredaste bredden 85 mm. I inläggen sitter 8
svarta hyskor och hakar. Tröjans vänstra framstycke kantad med ett 4 mm brett
vävt band. Likaså är skörtens ytterkanter och ärmens sprund och axelkarmarna
kantade med detta band. Framstyckena har vardera 3 parallellt snedställda 40
mm breda guldbårder. Bredd mellan bårderna 30 mm. Ärmarna och ryggstycket har
även snedställda bårder. Den 15 mm breda guldbården förekommer på kragen,
längs med axelsöm och ärmsöm. På axelkarmarna längs ärmarnas sömmar, på
skörten mitt bak och längs med sidorna.Tyget är uppskuret mellan bårderna.
Under slitsarna skymtar guldbroderierna på mörk gulorange guldbrokad.
Guldbroderierna består av växtmotiv med paljetter. På skörtens överkant 7 st
hål kantade med gult silke utom de 2 skörten vid framkanterna som har 4 st
hål. Ärmsprunden är 185 mm långa. Längs med sprunden 11 st 15 mm långa
knapphål sydda med gult silke. På kragens vänstra framkant 2 st flätade öglor
av gulmetall. Längd 24 mm. En kil under höger ärmhåla. Höjd 85 mm, bredd 55
mm. Längs med båda framstyckena 2 st parallella 15 mm breda guldbårder av lan,
kantiljer och paljetter. Avståndet mellan bårderna 4 mm. Tröjan fodrad med
naturfärgat linne. Framstyckena har infodringar av brunt siden. I
infodringarna 2 bruna sidenband. Längd 155 mm, bredd 5 mm. Det högra bandet i
form av en ögla. Kragen, ärmarna samt skörten fodrade med brunt siden.

description: ['metro station in Vienna, Austria', 'bridge']
parsed caption:
Richtung Nordosten zur [Brücke über die
Zeile](https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Br%C3%BCcke_%C3%BCber_die_Zeile
"de:Brücke über die Zeile"), die beiden mit
[Stromschienen](https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stromschiene "de:Stromschiene")
elektrifizierten Gleise, die in Bildmitte in den Tunnel führen, gehören zur
Wientallinie Richtung Hütteldorf, die von der [U-Bahn-Linie
U4](https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/U-Bahn-Linie_4_\(Wien\) "de:U-Bahn-Linie 4
\(Wien\)") bedient wird.  
Die steile Rampe zur _Brücke über die Zeile_ wurde mit dem Bahnhof
Längenfeldgasse in der bestehenden Form erst 1989 für die Weiterführung der
Linie U6 zum Bahnhof Meidling gebaut, vorher lag die Trennung von Wiental- und
Gürtellinie weiter westlich am Bahnhof Meidling Hauptstraße und die Rampe war
passend zum Dampflokomotiv- und Fernbahnbetrieb zu Anfang des 20. Jahrhunderts
deutlich flacher. Die Streckengleise der Wientallinie lagen an dieser Stelle
links unmittelbar neben der Ufermauer zum Wienkanal.

description: ['museum in Firdgum, Netherlands', 'inside part of a three-dimensional object']
parsed caption:
In Firdgum is een zodenhuis nagebouwd op grond van vondsten in terpen en
wierden, zoals bijvoorbeeld in Leens, waar hele zodenmuren in de terp werden
aangetroffen. Ook is bij het bouwen informatie van zodenhuizen in Noorwegen
gebruikt. Desalniettemin stortte het eerste zodenhuis in in het najaar van
2013 , het jaar waarin het werd gebouwd. In 2015 werd een nieuwe poging gedaan
waarbij het dak over de muren stak en het regenwater niet meer in het muren
inwaterde. Deze foto toont een deel van het interieur van dat zodenhuis,
vermoedelijk een kookplaats.

Camera: Zenit 3M Film: Ilford FP4 plus 125 ISO

Flits: Panasonic PE-145

description: ['comet']
parsed caption:
In the past comets brought with them connotations of doom and gloom.
Witnessing a comet in the night sky could very well be one of the scariest
things a person might see up there in the heavens. Nowadays, given sufficient
distance from the Earth, comets elicit a distinctly different reaction. People
gaze at them in wonder from even bright city skies- and amateur astronomers
enjoy the change in pace from their usual astronomical vistas. This comet,
LINEAR (C/2002 T7), rounded the Sun in 2004 and began its journey to the outer
part of the solar system. On its way, people in the northern hemisphere were
able to catch a glimpse of it during the subsequent months.The images shown
here are separated by 3-4 days worth of time. Notice how quickly the comet
changes its appearance. Also note how the comet's anti-solar direction (along
the tail) is changing as it moves in its orbit (the images have identical
orientations with North at the left). This image was taken as part of Advanced
Observing Program (AOP) program during 2014 at Kitt Peak Visitor Center.
